I&#39;ve released a new version of the Concordion acceptance testing
framework to support JUnit 4.4. Example:

HTML:

&lt;html xmlns:concordion=&quot;http://www.concordion.org/2007/concordion&quot;&gt;
     &lt;body&gt;
         &lt;p&gt;
             The greeting for user
             &lt;span concordion:set=&quot;#firstName&quot;&gt;Bob&lt;/span&gt;
             will be:
             &lt;span
concordion:assertEquals=&quot;greetingFor(#firstName)&quot;&gt;Hello Bob!&lt;/span&gt;
         &lt;/p&gt;
     &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;


JUnit 4.4:

import org.concordion.integration.junit4.ConcordionRunner;
import org.junit.runner.RunWith;

@RunWith(ConcordionRunner.class)
public class Demo {

     public String greetingFor(String firstName) {
         return String.format(&quot;Hello %s!&quot;, firstName);
     }
}


See:  http://www.concordion.org &lt;http://www.concordion.org&gt;

